I haven't decided yet, it's just an idea. Perhaps Cinema or other Visual Arts.
Honestly, the one I'd like to do the most is related to the Arts... but I am not sure that's a viable Career option.

It's not that I can't. I DO have Time as I am not really doing anything. I am Afraid of wasting Time doing Jobs that I Don't really like. I feel like I should follow a more "focused" approach. You know what I mean?
But I can't waste too much Time find a Job, otherwise I won't do what I TRULY Like.
I am not sure, I'd need to be lucky and find one that I like randomly.
I Don't know what route to take, though.
I suppose I like the Arts. Sort of.
